Former Cabinet Secretary for Sports Hassan Wario is set to be prosecuted over the misuse of the Rio 2016 Olympic funds amounting to 55 million KenyaÂ shillings. In a statement, the director of Public Prosecution Noordin Haji indicated that Wario, alongside six other officials will face six counts of abuse of office and four counts of wilful failure to comply with laws relating to the management of public funds. 